{"to":["oakwood-owlets-parents@example.com"],"subject":"Oakwood Owlets – Coordinating Our Group Project (Science Fair due Mar 15)","body":"Hi Owlets parents,

I hope you’re all doing well. As we head into the final month before the Science Fair (our project is due Friday, 15 March), I’d like to start coordinating the Oakwood Owlets’ group project so every family knows what’s needed and when.

Snapshot of the plan
• Goal: Build an interactive “Mini Weather Station” display.
• Key deadlines:
   – Draft research outline: Friday, 22 Feb
   – Materials purchased: Friday, 1 Mar
   – Display assembly: Fri–Sun, 8–10 Mar
   – Practice presentations: Tue–Thu, 12–14 Mar
• Suggested parent task groups:
   1. Research & Sourcing – help kids collect data, print graphs, gather background facts.
   2. Build & Design – assist with constructing the display board and model housing.
   3. Rehearsal Coaching – listen to practice runs and offer feedback.

Proposed kickoff Zoom: Monday, 19 Feb @ 7:30 pm (feel free to suggest an alternate time if this clashes with other commitments).

Action items for you
1. Reply with the task group(s) you’re comfortable helping with.
2. Confirm your availability for the kickoff call or propose another slot.
3. Let me know of any materials or tools you can supply (poster board, sensors, craft supplies, etc.).

I’ll circulate a shared Google Sheet once the volunteer list is set so everyone can track progress and sign up for specific tasks.

Thank you all so much for your enthusiasm and support—our Owlets are going to do great!

Best regards,

[Your Name]
Parent Coordinator, Oakwood Owlets
[phone number]"}
